Cherashore Survey Analysis

PennPraxis

8/8/2022

Overview

The following data represents outputs from a survey aimed at studying community sentiments regarding programming and design at Cherashore Playground. The survey was conducted by PennPraxis and ImapactEd in summer 2021/2022.

Key Takeaways

  • We collected 43 in-person survey responses that were valid and more than 2/3rds complete. Response per survey-hour was very low.
  • Participants were mostly Black, in the 25-44 year age bracket and visited to Cherashore by car
  • Participants expressed strong interest for continued and additional attention to the youth sports, the pool, and facilities in the recreation center
  • Generally, participants feel safe, gather at Cherashore with their friends and family

How To Use This Document

This is an ‘R Markdown’ document designed to provide a more readable and dynamic interface for outputs from data analysis done using the statistical software language R.

You can use the table of contents at left to navigate through the document.

Expand the document to fit the maximum extent of your screen to make sure you can see the content of the plots.

Section 8 in particular highlights community sentiment by age group and proximity to Cherashore. We can create additional cross-tabulations if needed.

This is an internal document and not for distribution.

This document is designed to allow for exploration of all survey data collected.

1. Frequency of Use

How often do you visit Cherashore?

summary <- dat %>% 
  group_by(X1Frequency.of.Use) %>% 
  filter(X1Frequency.of.Use != "") %>% 
  summarise(count=n()) %>% 
  mutate(X1Frequency.of.Use_perc = (count/sum(count))*100)

ggplot(summary %>%
         select(X1Frequency.of.Use_perc, X1Frequency.of.Use), 
         aes(x=X1Frequency.of.Use_perc, y=X1Frequency.of.Use)) + 
  geom_bar(stat="identity", width = 0.3, fill="#4198A1")+
  labs(
    x="Percent (%)",
    y="Response",
    subtitle="n = 28 (unique responses)"
  )+
  plotTheme12ptY
